25|$|On 16 November the 32nd {{became the}} first U.S. forces to launch a <b>ground</b> <b>assault</b> against Japanese forces. They were {{followed}} by the 163rd Regimental Combat Team of the 41st Infantry Division, which arrived at Port Moresby, New Guinea on 27 December, and whose first elements flew over the Owen Stanley Range to the Buna Gona front on 30 December. On the Atlantic front, the first units {{to engage in a}} <b>ground</b> <b>assault</b> were the 1st Infantry, 3rd Infantry, 9th Infantry, 1st Armored and the 2nd Armored Divisions in North Africa on 8 November.|$|R
